ers/martinszeltins","html_url":"https://github.com/martinszeltins","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martinszeltins/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martinszeltins/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martinszeltins/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martinszeltins/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martinszeltins/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martinszeltins/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martinszeltins/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martinszeltins/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/martinszeltins/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":6005789711,"node_id":"LA_kwDOKYE-bc8AAAABZfkUDw","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/victorgarciaesgi/regle/labels/bug%20%F0%9F%90%9E","name":"bug 🐞","color":"b60205","default":false,"description":"Something isn't working"},{"id":7946252650,"node_id":"LA_kwDOKYE-bc8AAAAB2aIxag","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/victorgarciaesgi/regle/labels/nuxt%20%E2%9B%B0%EF%B8%8F","name":"nuxt ⛰️","color":"3BD548","default":false,"description":"Issue is related to `@regle/nuxt` package"}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":7,"created_at":"2026-05-05T08:28:55Z","updated_at":"2026-05-20T16:15:07Z","closed_at":"2026-05-20T16:15:07Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### Reproduction\n\nN/A\n\n### Steps to reproduce the bug\n\nI am running and developing my app in Docker. I wanted to use the [setupFile](https://reglejs.dev/integrations/nuxt#setupfile) to define global configuration. But when I did that, I noticed that `useRegle` became unrecognized. I started digging around what caused the issue. I reproduced a clean project, outside Docker and it worked. Then I noticed in `.nuxt/regle-exports.ts` was showing a problem:\n\n```ts\nimport ReglePlugin from \"/app/app/common/config/nuxt/regle.nuxt.config\";\n                                                       ^^^^^^^^^^^\n    Cannot find module '/app/app/common/config/nuxt/regle.nuxt.config' or its corresponding type declarations.ts(2307)\n```\n\nI replaced the path with relative and it started working again. `../app/common/config/nuxt/regle.nuxt.config`\n\n<img width=\"1171\" height=\"550\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/8af2f94c-0506-4128-9489-9d5a7a70ad31\" />\n\nMy `nuxt.config.ts`:\n\n```ts\nexport default defineNuxtConfig({\n    modules: ['@regle/nuxt'],\n    \n    regle: {\n        setupFile: '~/common/config/nuxt/regle.nuxt.config.ts',\n    },\n})\n```\n\nI looked inside source code and found [packages/nuxt/src/module.ts](https://github.com/victorgarciaesgi/regle/blob/main/packages/nuxt/src/module.ts#L38-L69) these lines that are causing the problem and generating the wrong path:\n\n```ts\nconst setupFilePathOS = await resolvePath(options.setupFile);\n// Ensure the path is normalized for POSIX compatibility (https://github.com/victorgarciaesgi/regle/issues/152)\n\nif (setupFilePathOS) {\n  const relativePath = resolve(setupFilePathOS);\n\n  const setupFilePathWithoutExtension = path.join(\n    path.dirname(relativePath),\n    path.basename(relativePath, path.extname(relativePath))\n  );\n\n  const setupFilePathWithoutExtensionCleaned = path.posix.normalize(\n    setupFilePathWithoutExtension.replaceAll(/\\\\/gi, '/')\n  );\n\n  const template = addTemplate({\n    filename: 'regle-exports.ts',\n    write: true,\n    getContents: () => `\nimport type { InferRegleRules, RegleCustomFieldStatus } from '@regle/core';\nimport ReglePlugin from \"${setupFilePathWithoutExtensionCleaned}\";\n```\nThis generates an absolute path for **ReglePlugin** import which breaks **useRegle** when running in Docker. It should instead generate a relative path.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nN/A\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nN/A\n\n### Environment information\n\n- `@regle/x` version: 1.24.0\n- `vue` version: 3.5.33\n- `typescript` version: 5.9.3\n- `Nuxt` version (if you use Nuxt): 4.4.4\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/victorgarciaesgi/regle/issues/344/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/victorgarciaesgi/regle/issues/344/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nuxt/ui/issues/6465","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nuxt/ui","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nuxt/ui/issues/6465/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nuxt/ui/issues/6465/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nuxt/ui/issues/6465/events","html_url":"https://github.com/nuxt/ui/issues/6465","id":4485241369,"node_id":"I_kwDOGYfKK88AAAABC1daGQ","number":6465,"title":"MD document code examples are missing a large amount of implementation details","user":{"login":"uovol","id":22807971,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIyODA3OTcx","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/22807971?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/uovol","html_url":"https://github.com/uovol","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/uovol/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/uovol/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/uovol/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/uovol/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/uovol/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/uovol/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/uovol/repo