tils-repro\n\n`nuxt.config.ts`:\n```ts\nexport default defineNuxtConfig({\n  modules: ['@nuxtjs/i18n'],\n  i18n: {\n    defaultLocale: 'en',\n    locales: [{ code: 'en', file: 'en.json' }],\n    lazy: true,\n    langDir: 'i18n/locales/',\n  },\n})\n```\n\n`components/Hello.vue`:\n```vue\n<template>\n  <p>{{ t('greeting') }}</p>\n</template>\n<script setup lang=\"ts\">\nconst { t } = useI18n()\n</script>\n```\n\n`i18n/locales/en.json`:\n```json\n{ \"greeting\": \"Hello World\" }\n```\n\n`tests/hello.spec.ts`:\n```ts\nimport { mountSuspended } from '@nuxt/test-utils/runtime'\nimport Hello from '../components/Hello.vue'\n\nit('renders translated greeting', async () => {\n  const wrapper = await mountSuspended(Hello)\n  expect(wrapper.text()).toContain('Hello World')\n})\n```\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nWhen using `mountSuspended` from `@nuxt/test-utils`, locale files configured with `lazy: true` fail to load. Keys that exist in `en.json` are returned as raw key strings instead of translated values.\n\nThe root cause: `.nuxt/i18n.options.mjs` wires locale loading through virtual modules that depend on the `@nuxtjs/i18n` Vite plugin being active. The `@nuxt/test-utils` runtime skips the full Vite plugin setup, so when the loader calls `load()` at runtime the import fails and the vue-i18n instance is left empty for the entire test run.\n\nI intend to submit a PR for this and would like to confirm the fix direction is acceptable before writing code.\n\n### Additional context\n\nRelated issues:\n- https://github.com/nuxt-modules/i18n/issues/3827\n- https://github.com/nuxt-modules/i18n/issues/2637\n\n### Logs\n\n```\nFailed locale loading: Cannot find module '/i18n/i18n/locales/en.json?import'\n  imported from virtual:nuxt:.../.nuxt/i18n.options.mjs\n[intlify] Not found 'greeting' key in 'en' locale messages.\n```","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nuxt-modules/i18n/issues/3982/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0