,"type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2026-05-07T17:40:22Z","updated_at":"2026-05-22T13:18:02Z","closed_at":"2026-05-22T13:18:02Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Summary\n\nTwo related, narrow defects around the `i18n.vueI18n` option:\n\n1. **Silent skip in production builds** — when the configured `vueI18n` file cannot be resolved, the warning that flags the misconfiguration is gated behind `import.meta.dev`. In `nuxt build` the file is silently ignored, no warning, no error, the production bundle just lacks `pluralRules` / overrides without any feedback.\n2. **API option docs do not mention path resolution semantics** — the path is resolved relative to `i18nDir` (`restructureDir`), not to the project root or `nuxt.config.ts`, but the [`vueI18n` API option page](https://i18n.nuxtjs.org/docs/api/options#vuei18n) does not state this. New users naturally expect a path relative to `nuxt.config.ts`.\n\nI'm not asking to change resolution semantics (that was discussed in #3399 / #3394 / #3395 and won't-fixed). I'm asking for **diagnostics + docs** that surface the existing semantics earlier.\n\n## Reproduction\n\n`@nuxtjs/i18n@10.2.3`, Nuxt `4.2.2`, Vue I18n `11.4.2`.\n\n1. Place `i18n.config.ts` at the **project root** (next to `nuxt.config.ts`):\n   ```ts\n   export default defineI18nConfig(() => ({\n     legacy: false,\n     pluralRules: {\n       ru: (n) => {\n         if (n === 0) return 0\n         const lt = n % 100, ld = n % 10, teen = lt >= 11 && lt <= 19\n         if (!teen && ld === 1) return 1\n         if (!teen && ld >= 2 && ld <= 4) return 2\n         return 3\n       }\n     }\n   }))\n   ```\n2. In `nuxt.config.ts`:\n   ```ts\n   i18n: {\n     vueI18n: './i18n.config.ts',\n     // ...\n   }\n   ```\n3. Run `nuxt build`.\n\n**Observed**:\n- `nuxt build` exits 0 with no warnings, no errors.\n- Inspecting `.nuxt/dist/server/client.manifest.mjs` and `.nuxt/dist/client/_nuxt/*.js`: the config file is **not** referenced anywhere; the `pluralRules` chunk is missing.\n- Runtime translations silently fall back to default `pluralDefault` rule, breaking russian plurals in production while everything looked fine locally (because `nuxt dev` printed a warning that the developer may or may not have noticed).\n\n**After moving the file to `i18n/i18n.config.ts`**: it is picked up correctly, compiled into a separate chunk, registered in `vueI18nConfigs`, and `pluralRules.ru` works as expected.\n\n## Source pointers\n\nThe warn is gated to dev only:\n\nhttps://github.com/nuxt-modules/i18n/blob/main/src/layers.ts (the resolver) — equivalent in the installed v10.2.3 (`node_modules/@nuxtjs/i18n/dist/module.mjs:1590-1592`):\n\n```js\nconst resolved = await resolveVueI18nConfigInfo(i18nDir, i18n?.vueI18n);\nif (import.meta.dev && resolved == null && i18n?.vueI18n) {\n  logger.warn(`Vue I18n configuration file \\`${i18n.vueI18n}\\` not found in \\`${i18nDir}\\`. Skipping...`);\n}\nreturn resolved;\n```\n\n`resolveVueI18nConfigInfo`'s `cwd` is the layer's `i18nDir`, so any `./relative` user-supplied path is resolved against `i18nDir`, not the project root.\n\n## Proposed fixes (any subset)\n\n1. **Drop the `import.meta.dev` gate** — emit the warn (or fail the build) when `vueI18n` was explicitly set but didn't resolve. A deliberate `vueI18n` value that doesn't exist is almost always a misconfiguration the user wants to know about.\n2. **Or**: emit a structured `consola.warn` that surfaces in CI logs of `nuxt build` even if downgraded, so users notice via build output.\n3. **Docs**: add one sentence to https://i18n.nuxtjs.org/docs/api/options#vuei18n: \"The path is resolved relative to `i18nDir` (default: `i18n/`), not to `nuxt.config.ts`. Use an absolute path if you want to escape the i18n directory.\"\n\nI'm happy to send the docs PR if the maintainers prefer.\n\n## Prior art (not duplicates of this report)\n\n- #3399 — closed won't-fix: resolution semantics will not change. Acknowledged.\n- #3394 — closed: \"documented in migration guide\". The migration guide is helpful, but the API page itself is silent.\n- #3395 — closed: same as #3394.\n\nThis report is **not** about changing semantics. It is about (a) catching misconfiguration in production builds, and (b) putting the resolution rule on the API page where new users actually look first.\n\n## Environment\n\n- Nuxt 4.2.2\n- @nuxtjs/i18n 10.2.3\n- vue-i18n 11.4.2\n- Node 24.x\n- Build: `nuxt build` (production)\n- OS: macOS\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nuxt-modules/i18n/issues/3983/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nuxt-modules/i18n/issues/3983/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/npmx-dev/npmx.dev/issues/2719","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/npmx-dev/npmx.dev","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/npmx-dev/npmx.dev/issues/2719/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/npmx-dev/npmx.dev/issues/2719/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/npmx-dev/npmx.dev/issues/2719/events","html_url":"https://github.com/npmx-dev/npmx.dev/issues/2719","id":4424279397,"node_id":"I_kwDOQ_ILBs8AAAABB7UlZQ","number":2719,"title":"Org tooltip in package name is hidden behind package subheader","user":{"login":"mootari","id":322014,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMyMjAxNA==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/322014?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/mootari","html_url":"https