t":false,"description":"設定・ツール・依存関係の変更"}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2026-05-19T12:27:15Z","updated_at":"2026-05-19T13:16:49Z","closed_at":"2026-05-19T13:16:49Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"OWNER","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## 概要\n\nPR 作成・push 時に Claude Code が自動でコードレビューを行う仕組みを GitHub Actions で導入する。slack-board (80-cloud/slack-board PR #2) で先行導入 + 動作検証済の構成を、recipe-board の Rails + Nuxt 3 スタック向けに調整して導入する。\n\n## 動機\n\n- スクール課題提出物の品質担保\n- マルチプロジェクト学習における横断的なレビュー観点の統一\n- セキュリティ・パフォーマンス・設計判断のリアルタイム可視化\n\n## 実装内容\n\n`.github/workflows/` に 2 ファイルを追加 (既存の backend-ci.yml / frontend-ci.yml / gitleaks.yml / rds-auto-stop.yml と並列共存):\n\n1. `claude-code-review.yml` — PR open / synchronize で自動レビュー (sticky comment)\n2. `claude.yml` — @claude メンションで対話レビュー\n\nレビュー観点は recipe-board の技術スタック (Ruby on Rails / Nuxt 3 / MySQL / AWS) に合わせて Rails・Nuxt 固有の論点に調整。\n\n## あとから user 側で必要な作業\n\n- GitHub Secrets に `CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN` を登録 (slack-board と同じ token を再利用可)\n- https://github.com/apps/claude で recipe-board を追加 (slack-board のとき All repositories を選んでいれば不要)\n\n## 関連\n\n- 先行 PR: https://github.com/80-cloud/slack-board/pull/2\n- 同時展開: https://github.com/80-cloud/hideharu-AI/pull/64 / https://github.com/80-cloud/sns-board/pull/212","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/80-cloud/recipe-board/issues/129/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/80-cloud/recipe-board/issues/129/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nuxt/test-utils/issues/1696","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nuxt/test-utils","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nuxt/test-utils/issues/1696/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nuxt/test-utils/issues/1696/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nuxt/test-utils/issues/1696/events","html_url":"https://github.com/nuxt/test-utils/issues/1696","id":4422393045,"node_id":"I_kwDOC-k6cs8AAAABB5hc1Q","number":1696,"title":"setupNuxt crashes on `nuxtApp._route.sync` when `_route` is missing (Nuxt 4 + Vitest 4)","user":{"login":"jcfauchet","id":21689610,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIxNjg5NjEw","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/21689610?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/jcfauchet","html_url":"https://github.com/jcfauchet","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jcfauchet/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jcfauchet/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jcfauchet/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jcfauchet/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jcfauchet/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jcfauchet/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jcfauchet/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jcfauchet/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jcfauchet/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":6280264035,"node_id":"LA_kwDOC-k6cs8AAAABdlU5Yw","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nuxt/test-utils/labels/pending%20triage","name":"pending triage","color":"5D08F5","default":false,"description":""}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":4,"created_at":"2026-05-11T16:13:34Z","updated_at":"2026-05-12T12:35:00Z","closed_at":"2026-05-12T12:35:00Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### Environment\n\n  - Operating System: Darwin 24.6.0\n  - Node Version: v22\n  - Nuxt Version: 4.2.2\n  - Package Manager: pnpm@10.33.0\n  - @nuxt/test-utils: 4.0.3\n  - vitest: 4.1.5\n  - @vitest/coverage-istanbul: 4.1.5\n  - Vue: 3.5.27\n  - Runtime Modules: @nuxtjs/apollo, @nuxtjs/i18n\n\n### Reproduction\n\n Minimal repro derived from examples/app-vitest:\n\n  vitest.config.ts:\n\n  ```\nimport { defineVitestProject } from '@nuxt/test-utils/config'\n  import { defineConfig } from 'vitest/config'\n\n  export default defineConfig({\n    test: {\n      projects: [\n        await defineVitestProject({\n          test: {\n            name: 'happy-dom',\n            environment: 'happy-dom', // hard-overridden to 'nuxt' by defineVitestProject v4 (config.mjs:231)\n            include: ['**/*.test.ts'],\n            setupFiles: ['./setup.ts'],\n          },\n        }),\n      ],\n    },\n  })\n```\n\n  setup.ts:\n\n  ```\nimport { mockNuxtImport } from '@nuxt/test-utils/runtime'\n\n  mockNuxtImport('useNuxtApp', () => () => ({\n    hooks: { hookOnce: vi.fn((_event, handler) => handler()) },\n    callHook: vi.fn(),\n    // no `_route` — user-land has no reason to mock a private internal\n  }))\n```\n\n  smoke.test.ts:\n\n  ```\ndescribe('smoke', () => {\n    test('runs', () => {\n      expect(true).toBe(true)\n    })\n  })\n```\n\n  Happy to share a public branch if a real-world repro helps.\n\n  Field 3 — Describe the bug\n\n  Every test file fails in the `beforeAll(setupNuxt)` hook injected by `runtime/entry.mjs`:\n\n  ```\n  TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'sync')\n   ❯ sync node_modules/@nuxt/test-utils/dist/runtime/shared/nuxt.mjs:7:27\n        5|   const nuxtApp = useNuxtApp();\n        6|   function sync() {\n        7|     return nuxtApp._route.sync ? nuxtApp._route.sync() : nuxtApp.callH…\n         |                           ^\n        8|   }\n   ❯ setupNuxt node_modules/@nuxt/test-utils/dist/runtime/shared/nuxt.mjs:14:10\n   ❯ node_modules/@nuxt/test-utils/dist/runtime/entry.mjs:5:5\n  ```\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nEvery test file fails in the `beforeAll(setupNuxt)` hook injected by `runtime/entry.mjs`:\n\n  ```\n  TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'sync')\n   ❯ sync node_modules/@nuxt/test-utils/dist/runtime/shared/nuxt.mjs:7:27\n        5|   const nuxtApp = useNuxtApp();\n        6|   function sync() {\n        7|     return nuxtApp._route.sync ? nuxtApp._route.sync() : nuxtApp.callH…\n         |                           ^\n        8|   }\n   ❯ setupNuxt node_modules/@nuxt/test-utils/dist/runtime/shared/nuxt.mjs:14:10\n   ❯ node_modules/@nuxt/test-utils/dist/runtime/entry.mjs:5:5\n  ```\n\n  ### Root cause\n\n  `dist/runtime/shared/nuxt.mjs`:\n\n  ```js\n  export async function setupNuxt() {\n    const { useRouter } = await import(\"#app/composables/router\");\n    await import(\"#app/nuxt-vitest-app-entry\").then((r) => r.default());\n    const nuxtApp = useNuxtApp();\n    function sync() {\n      return nuxtApp._route.sync ? nuxtApp._route.sync() : nuxtApp.callHook(\"page:finish\");\n      //              ^^^^^^^^^^^^^ throws when `_route` is undefined\n    }\n    // …\n  }\n  ```\n\n  `nuxtApp._route` is a **private internal** populated by Nuxt's vue-router plugin during app init. It is legitimately\n   `undefined` in at least three scenarios:\n\n  1. The test bootstrap (`#app/nuxt-vitest-app-entry`) doesn't initialize the vue-router plugin — no real navigation\n  needed in unit tests.\n  2. The user mocks `useNuxtApp` via `mockNuxtImport`. Public Nuxt APIs surface `$router` / `$route`; the internal\n  `_route` (with underscore) is undocumented and user mocks legitimately omit it.\n  3. `_route` is private (underscore prefix), so accessing it across Nuxt versions without `?.` is brittle by design.\n\n  The existing `nuxtApp.callHook(\"page:finish\")` fallback shows the authors intended to support the case where\n  `_route.sync` is absent — they just didn't cover the case where `_route` itself is absent.\n\n  ### Why it didn't surface in v3\n\n  `defineVitestProject` v4 [hard-overrides `test.environment = \n  'nuxt'`](https://github.com/nuxt/test-utils/blob/v4.0.3/src/config.ts) regardless of what callers pass. In v3,\n  callers could keep `'happy-dom'`, `__NUXT_VITEST_ENVIRONMENT__` was never set, and `runtime/entry.mjs` skipped\n  `setupNuxt` for non-`.nuxt.test.ts` files. In v4 every test file runs `setupNuxt`, exposing the crash.\n\n  ### Proposed fix — defensive optional chaining\n\n  ```diff\n  diff --git a/src/runtime/shared/nuxt.ts b/src/runtime/shared/nuxt.ts\n  @@ -4,7 +4,7 @@ export async function setupNuxt() {\n     await import('#app/nuxt-vitest-app-entry').then((r) => r.default())\n     const nuxtApp = useNuxtApp()\n     function sync() {\n  -    return nuxtApp._route.sync ? nuxtApp._route.sync() : nuxtApp.callHook('page:finish')\n  +    return nuxtApp?._route?.sync ? nuxtApp._route.sync() : nuxtApp?.callHook?.('page:finish')\n     }\n  ```\n\n  Validated locally via `pnpm patch @nuxt/test-utils@4.0.3` on a 611-test-file Nuxt 4 / Vitest 4 codebase — unblocks 6\n   test files that were previously crashing, no regression elsewhere. Not planning to submit a PR unless asked, but\n  happy to.\n\n### Additional context\n\nUser-side workaround **does not work**: prepending a `vi.mock('#app/nuxt', …)` setup file before `runtime/entry.mjs`\n   either (a) gets registered too late because `entry.mjs` is `unshift`-ed to `setupFiles[0]` by\n  `defineVitestProject`, so `shared/nuxt.mjs`'s ESM binding to `useNuxtApp` is already frozen by the time our mock\n  registers, or (b) overrides the user's own `mockNuxtImport('useNuxtApp', …)` mock with an incomplete shape and\n  breaks every other test in the suite.\n\n  The only reliable workarounds we've found:\n  - `describe.skip` the affected files\n  - `pnpm patch @nuxt/test-utils@4.0.3` with the diff above\n\n  Adding `_route` to the user's `mockNuxtImport` factory **does not** help either — the mock applies to user-land\n  code, but `shared/nuxt.mjs`'s internal `useNuxtApp` call resolved before any user setup file ran.\n\n  ### Possibly related\n\n  May share root cause with users reporting `[nuxt] instance unavailable` / \"page:finish hangs\" on Nuxt 4 + Vitest 4\n  setups in plain `*.test.ts` files (non-`.nuxt.test.ts`).\n\n### Logs\n\n```shell-script\nFAIL  |happy-dom| src/domains/views/result-list/map/components/__tests__/ResultMap.test.ts\n  TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'sync')\n   ❯ sync ../../node_modules/.pnpm/@nuxt+test-utils@4.0.3_…/dist/runtime/shared/nuxt.mjs:7:27\n        5|   const nuxtApp = useNuxtApp();\n        6|   function sync() {\n        7|     return nuxtApp._route.sync ? nuxtApp._route.sync() : nuxtApp.callH…\n         |                           ^\n        8|   }\n        9|   const { hasNuxtPage } = getVueWrapperPlugin();\n   ❯ setupNuxt ../../node_modules/.pnpm/@nuxt+test-utils@4.0.3_…/dist/runtime/shared/nuxt.mjs:14:10\n   ❯ ../../node_modules/.pnpm/@nuxt+test-utils@4.0.3_…/dist/runtime/entry.mjs:5:5\n\n NB: the `|happy-dom|` prefix is the Vitest project `name` (set in our vitest.config.ts), not the runtime\n  environment. defineVitestProject silently overwrites `environment: 'happy-dom'` to `'nuxt'` (see config.mjs:231) —\n  confirmed by the deprecation warnings printed by `vitest-environment-nuxt` for every test file.\n```","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nuxt/test-utils/issues/1696/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nuxt/test-utils/issues/1696/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nuxt-modules/turnstile/issues/623","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/nuxt-modul